Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Zest the @lemon{1/2}(zested and cut into wedges) then chop into wedges. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Put the @British pork mince{240%g} in a #bowl{} along with the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @dried oregano{1%tsp}, half the garlic and half the lemon zest. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Use your hands to thoroughly mix then divide into 4 small balls per person. Pop on a #plate{} and set aside.

  > IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Peel the @potatoes{450%g} then chop into 2cm wide chips. Pop on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, spread out and roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Pop in a small bowl along with the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar{1%tsp} (see ingredients for amount). Season with @salt{}, stir to combine then set aside.

Trim the @cucumber{1/2}(trimmed and chopped) then halve lengthways. Chop each half into 4 long strips then chop widthways into small pieces. Trim the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}(root trimmed and sliced) then half lengthways. Thinly slice widthways. Chop the @medium tomato{2}(chopped into 2cm chunks). Pick the @mint{1%bunch}(leaves picked and chopped, stalks discarded) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. When hot, add the pork koftas and fry until browned and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}, turning often.

  > IMPORTANT: The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} and scatter over the potatoes for the final 5 mins of cooking time. When everything is almost cooked, pop the @plain naans{2} on a baking tray and sprinkle on a little water. Bake in your oven until warmed through, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the cucumber, remaining garlic, remaining lemon zest, @Greek style natural yoghurt{150%g} and half the mint in a bowl. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix and set aside.

  > This is your tzatziki

Put the tomatoes, @honey{15%g} and half the lemon juice in another bowl. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix and set aside.

To serve, pile all the toppings on the naans! Lettuce, chips, tomato salad, koftas, tzatziki and pickled onion - finish with the remaining mint and lemon.